{"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/s8CopyableP","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"],"type":"conformsTo"}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/labeledcontent"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI"]]},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:11OpenSwiftUI14LabeledContentV","modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"symbolKind":"struct","remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/LabelContent\/LabeledContent.swift#L140","fileName":"LabeledContent.swift"},"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"LabeledContent"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"LabeledContent"}],"platforms":[{"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"name":"iOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"10.15","unavailable":false,"name":"macOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"name":"tvOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"1.0","unavailable":false,"name":"visionOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"6.0","unavailable":false,"name":"watchOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false}],"roleHeading":"Structure","title":"LabeledContent"},"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LabeledContent\/init(content:label:)"],"generated":true},{"title":"Default Implementations","anchor":"Default-Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LabeledContent\/View-Implementations"],"generated":true}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LabeledContent"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"LabeledContent","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"Label","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Content","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The instance’s content represents a read-only or read-write value, and its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"label identifies or describes the purpose of that value."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The resulting element has a layout that’s consistent with other framework"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"controls and automatically adapts to its container, like a form or toolbar."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some styles of labeled content also apply styling or behaviors to the value"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"content, like making "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" views selectable."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The following example associates a label with a custom view and has","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a layout that matches the label of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Picker","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Form {","    LabeledContent(\"Custom Value\") {","        MyCustomView(value: $value)","    }","    Picker(\"Selected Value\", selection: $selection) {","        Text(\"Option 1\").tag(1)","        Text(\"Option 2\").tag(2)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Custom-view-labels","text":"Custom view labels","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can assemble labeled content with an explicit view for its label"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"using the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LabeledContent\/init(content:label:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" initializer. For example, you can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"rewrite the previous labeled content example using a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" view:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["LabeledContent {","    MyCustomView(value: $value)","} label: {","    Text(\"Custom Value\")","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"label"},{"text":" view builder accepts any kind of view, like a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Label"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["LabeledContent {","    MyCustomView(value: $value)","} label: {","    Label(\"Custom Value\", systemImage: \"hammer\")","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For cases where adding a subtitle to the label is desired, use a view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"builder that creates multiple "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Text"},{"type":"text","text":" views where the first text represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the title and the second text represents the subtitle:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["LabeledContent {","    MyCustomView(value: $value)","} label: {","    Text(\"Custom Value\")","    Text(\"Custom Subtitle Value\")","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Textual-labeled-content","text":"Textual labeled content","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can construct labeled content with string values or formatted values","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to create read-only displays of textual values:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Form {","    Section(\"Information\") {","        LabeledContent(\"Name\", value: person.name)","        LabeledContent(\"Age\", value: person.age, format: .number)","        LabeledContent(\"Height\", value: person.height,","            format: .measurement(width: .abbreviated))","    }","    if !person.pets.isEmpty {","        Section(\"Pets\") {","            ForEach(pet) { pet in","                LabeledContent(pet.species, value: pet.name)","            }","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Wherever possible, OpenSwiftUI makes this text selectable.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Compositional-elements","text":"Compositional elements","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can use labeled content as the label for other elements. For example,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a ","type":"text"},{"code":"NavigationLink","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" can present a summary value for the destination it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"links to:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Form {","    NavigationLink(value: Settings.wifiDetail) {","        LabeledContent(\"Wi-Fi\", value: ssidName)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In some cases, the styling of views used as the value content is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specialized as well. For example, while a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Toggle","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" in an inset group"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"form on macOS is styled as a switch by default, it’s styled as a checkbox"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when used as a value element within a surrounding "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LabeledContent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instance:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Form {","    LabeledContent(\"Source Control\") {","        Toggle(\"Refresh local status automatically\",","            isOn: $refreshLocalStatus)","        Toggle(\"Fetch and refresh server status automatically\",","            isOn: $refreshServerStatus)","        Toggle(\"Add and remove files automatically\",","            isOn: $addAndRemoveFiles)","        Toggle(\"Select files to commit automatically\",","            isOn: $selectFiles)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Controlling-label-visibility","text":"Controlling label visibility","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A label communicates the identity or purpose of the value, which is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"important for accessibility. However, you might want to hide the label","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the display, and some controls or contexts may visually hide their label","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by default. The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/labelsHidden()","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" modifier allows controlling that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"visibility. The following example hides both labels, producing only a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group of the two value views:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Group {","    LabeledContent(\"Custom Value\") {","        MyCustomView(value: $value)","    }","    Picker(\"Selected Value\", selection: $selection) {","        Text(\"Option 1\").tag(1)","        Text(\"Option 2\").tag(2)","    }","}",".labelsHidden()"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Styling-labeled-content","text":"Styling labeled content","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can set label styles using the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/labeledContentStyle(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"modifier. You can also build custom styles using ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LabeledContentStyle","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A container for attaching a label to a value-bearing view."}],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/View/labeledContentStyle(_:)":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","title":"labeledContentStyle(_:)","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/view\/labeledcontentstyle(_:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/labeledContentStyle(_:)","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"labeledContentStyle","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP0aB2UIE19labeledContentStyleyQrqd__AD07LabeledgH0Rd__lFQO1Sqd__mfp","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets a style for labeled content."}]},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/s8CopyableP":{"title":"Swift.Copyable","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/s8CopyableP","type":"unresolvable"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui","title":"OpenSwiftUI","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare the user interface and behavior for